IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: CommuniCare Health Centers is a private, non-profit health care organization providing comprehensive medical and dental services, substance abuse treatment, behavioral health services, and health education throughout Yolo County at four community clinic sites located in Davis, Woodland, Esparto, and West Sacramento. Since 1972, CommuniCare has been promoting healthy communities by providing affordable and culturally competent health care for those in need. CommuniCare Health Centers is a Federally Qualified Health Center (FQHC).
IRS990.MissionDesc: CommuniCare Health Centers' mission is to provide comprehensive and high quality health care to anyone in our community regardless of insurance status or ability to pay. Our mission is characterized by the following commitments: We deliver health care in a supportive, safe environment emphasizing patient partnership, wellness and preventive health in all of our services. We value the importance of a teaching and learning environment at all levels of the organization. We are committed to the underlying philosophy that health care is a right, not a privilege. In fulfillment of CommuniCare Health Centers' mission, total patient medical visits during the year reached 60,089; the number of patients 16,046; total mental health visits during the year reached 42,542 to total patients of 4,383; total dental visits reached 18,752 to total patients of 9,342. Health Education & community outreach encounters totaled 9,670.
IRS990.Desc: CommuniCare operates three primary care centers at carefully chosen locations to provide the best access to healthcare for Yolo county residents who cannot afford the full cost of healthcare and have no health insurance. Services include primary care, reproductive health, pediatric and adolescent services. Clinical facilities are located in Davis, West Sacramento, and Woodland. Visits totaled 57,865; total patients served was 15,192.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: Perinatal Services - A full spectrum of pre and post natal care, births health education, nutrition counseling, and social work support for low-income and indigent women of Yolo county. The program is a certified California Perinatal Services Program (CPSP). Services are offered at five facilities in Davis, West Sacramento, Woodland, Winters and Dixon with births at Sutter Davis Hospital. Visits totaled 10,589 and births at Sutter Davis Hospital totaled over 557.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: Behavioral Health Services is an outpatient substance abuse treatment program which offers medically assisted withdrawal and treatment to adults and adolescents involved with methamphetamine, opiates, and marijuana in groups and one on one counseling. Additionally, this department now offers life counseling services provided by licensed clinical social workers. Services are offered at three CommuniCare facilities: Davis, West Sacramento and Woodland. Visits totaled 36,011, serving over 3,950 patients.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: Dental Program- Acute and preventive dental care is provided for children and adults. Services include complete oral exams, X-Rays, Fillings, Root canals, Surgery, Gum Therapy, and specialty referrals. Services are provided at four sites in Yolo County: Davis, West Sacramento, Woodland and Esparto. CommuniCare also visits schools, child care centers and health fairs offering free exams, sealants and oral education materials. Visits totaled over 18,875.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Center has been recognized by the Internal Revenue Service as a non-profit corporation as described in Sec. 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code (IRC) and is exempt from federal and state income taxes on related income pursuant to Sec. 501(a) of the IRC and California Revenue and Taxation code Section 23701(d). Accordingly, no provision for income taxes is included in the accompanying financial statements. The tax years of 2015 through 2017 remain open and subject to examination by the appropriate government agencies in the United States and California.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The CFO and Finance Committee review the Form 990 and submits it to the board for approval. Once the form has been approved by the board, the CFO signs Form 8453 EO to authorize the CPA to E-file the return.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Board members and key employees are required to disclose conflicts of interest as soon as they become aware that a conflict may exist. The remaining board members evaluate the situation and the individual must either resign or excuse themselves from any discussions that involve the agency and the area of conflict.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Board of Directors maintains a Personnel Committee to review and update the Personnel Policies & Procedures Manual annually; With the Executive Committee, conducts the Chief Executive Officer's annual evaluation process; Reviews and approves the employee benefit package; Participates in formal employee Grievance Procedure when necessary.
